<body>
    <h1>
        1.2.2 Adding Tokens
    </h1>

    <p>
        Minilang tokens consist of the reserved words of the <a href="../language/syntax.html">language</a>, the tokens for literals 
        and the tokens for the operator and punctuation symbols.
    </p>

    <p>
        The token file syntax is described in <a href="../../syntax/lexer.html#token-file-syntax">this</a> document.
    </p>

    <p>
        To add tokens to the minilang language:
    </p>

    <ul>
        <li>
            Right-click your project in the Solution Explorer and select 'Add | New Item...'.
        </li>
        <li>
            Select Visual C++ | Utility | Text File (.txt) item and name the file <span class="mono">minilang.token</span>.
        </li>
        <li>
            Add the following code to the token file:<br />
			<ref file="ref/minilang.token.div"/>
        </li>
    </ul>
</body>
</html>